rComments: Midterms were all on ancient texts, some mentioned briefly in lecture. They hardly had anything to do with subject Women in Antiquity, if it did it was a reach. Definitions on midterms never had anything to do with the subject, again if it did it was a reach. Had hoped it would be about historical women in antiquity, more cultural history.
The material was focused strictly on her opinions and studies. Was not very clear in the lectures. Seemed cold, although she did attempt to joke around.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I took this course last year, but I have to disagree with some of the other comments. She is not rude nor selfish; I guess her German-ness/bluntness is a little off-putting for some, but I think she's a great lecturer. She's very enthusiastic about what she's teaching and can be very helpful on a personal level.
Very smart. She knows all the dead languages, well rounded in history and literature of the classical period. She is fun, witty, and friendly.

We weren't allowed to use our laptops in class, which was an initial challenge for me as my penmanship is horrible. I loved how each lecture was on a distinct topic, and although it was hard to be there for three hours, it turned out to be a really easy course. I completely disagree with those who said otherwise. Bird Course.
She was horrible, her lectures were all over the place, mid term was BRUTAL! and she was not very approachable or nice to talk to. Avoid her class if she is teaching!

I really wish I dropped this class. The class should be called "Intro to Ancient Greek Language & Their relationship to Germany". She wastes class time talking about her personal interests, and will REEM you out if you so much as LOOK at your phone. Horrible prof who thinks she is a God in her field. Don't take her class. She is rude, and selfish.
Her lectures are interesting and always informative. She prohibits the use of mobile devices in her class, and she becomes adorably agitated if she catches a student texting.

Her lectures are fun and she keeps it interesting. Clear lecture notes. Her tests are very straight forward. Might have one or two passage identifications but generally if you attend class and pay attention, you'll be fine!
